    <item>
      <title>FOR</title>
      <link>https://www.montferret.dev/docs/fql/operators/high-level/for/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://www.montferret.dev/docs/fql/operators/high-level/for/</guid>
      <description>&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;for&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;#for&#34;&gt;&#xA;FOR&#xA;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The versatile FOR keyword can be used to iterate over a different collections like array, objects and set of HTML elements.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;for-in&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;#for-in&#34;&gt;&#xA;FOR-IN&#xA;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;columns&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;column is-full&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div id=&#34;code-318-text&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-text&#34; style=&#34;height: 80px;&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &#xA;FOR variableName IN expression&#xA;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;script&gt;&#xA;        document.addEventListener(&#39;DOMContentLoaded&#39;, function () {&#xA;            const editor = ace.edit(&#39;code-318-text&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setTheme(&#34;ace/theme/tomorrow_night&#34;);&#xA;            editor.session.setMode(&#34;ace/mode/&#34; + &#39;aql&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setOptions({&#xA;                readOnly: true,&#xA;                highlightActiveLine: false,&#xA;                highlightGutterLine: false,&#xA;                displayIndentGuides: false,&#xA;                printMargin: false&#xA;            });&#xA;            editor.renderer.$cursorLayer.element.style.display = &#34;none&#34;&#xA;        }, false);&#xA;    &lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;FOR-IN&lt;/code&gt; statement iterates through all entries of an array, object, or values that implement &lt;a href=&#34;%22https://github.com/MontFerret/ferret/blob/master/pkg/runtime/core/value.go#L22%22&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;Iterable&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; interface.&#xA;Each element returned by expression is visited exactly once. The current element is made available for further processing in the variable specified by &lt;code&gt;variableName&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>RETURN</title>
      <link>https://www.montferret.dev/docs/fql/operators/high-level/return/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://www.montferret.dev/docs/fql/operators/high-level/return/</guid>
      <description>&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;return&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;#return&#34;&gt;&#xA;RETURN&#xA;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;RETURN&lt;/code&gt; statement can be used to produce the result of a query. It is mandatory to specify a &lt;code&gt;RETURN&lt;/code&gt; statement at the end of each block in a data-selection query, otherwise the query will be invalid. Using &lt;code&gt;RETURN&lt;/code&gt; on the main level in data-modification queries is optional.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The general syntax for &lt;code&gt;RETURN&lt;/code&gt; is:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;columns&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;column is-full&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div id=&#34;code-339-text&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-text&#34; style=&#34;height: 80px;&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &#xA;RETURN expression&#xA;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;script&gt;&#xA;        document.addEventListener(&#39;DOMContentLoaded&#39;, function () {&#xA;            const editor = ace.edit(&#39;code-339-text&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setTheme(&#34;ace/theme/tomorrow_night&#34;);&#xA;            editor.session.setMode(&#34;ace/mode/&#34; + &#39;aql&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setOptions({&#xA;                readOnly: true,&#xA;                highlightActiveLine: false,&#xA;                highlightGutterLine: false,&#xA;                displayIndentGuides: false,&#xA;                printMargin: false&#xA;            });&#xA;            editor.renderer.$cursorLayer.element.style.display = &#34;none&#34;&#xA;        }, false);&#xA;    &lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The expression returned by &lt;code&gt;RETURN&lt;/code&gt; is produced for each iteration in the block the &lt;code&gt;RETURN&lt;/code&gt; statement is placed in. That means the result of a &lt;code&gt;RETURN&lt;/code&gt; statement is always an array when inside &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.montferret.dev/docs/fql/operators/high-level/for/&#34; title=&#34;FOR&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;FOR&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; loop.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>FILTER</title>
      <link>https://www.montferret.dev/docs/fql/operators/high-level/filter/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://www.montferret.dev/docs/fql/operators/high-level/filter/</guid>
      <description>&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;filter&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;#filter&#34;&gt;&#xA;FILTER&#xA;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;FILTER&lt;/code&gt; statement can be used to restrict the results to elements that match an arbitrary logical condition.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The general syntax for &lt;code&gt;FILTER&lt;/code&gt; is:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;columns&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;column is-full&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div id=&#34;code-149-text&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-text&#34; style=&#34;height: 80px;&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &#xA;FILTER expression&#xA;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;script&gt;&#xA;        document.addEventListener(&#39;DOMContentLoaded&#39;, function () {&#xA;            const editor = ace.edit(&#39;code-149-text&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setTheme(&#34;ace/theme/tomorrow_night&#34;);&#xA;            editor.session.setMode(&#34;ace/mode/&#34; + &#39;aql&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setOptions({&#xA;                readOnly: true,&#xA;                highlightActiveLine: false,&#xA;                highlightGutterLine: false,&#xA;                displayIndentGuides: false,&#xA;                printMargin: false&#xA;            });&#xA;            editor.renderer.$cursorLayer.element.style.display = &#34;none&#34;&#xA;        }, false);&#xA;    &lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;expression&lt;/code&gt; must be a condition that evaluates to either false or true. If the condition result is false, the current element is skipped, so it will not be processed further and not be part of the result. If the condition is true, the current element is not skipped and can be further processed. See &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.montferret.dev/docs/fql/operators/&#34; title=&#34;Operators&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;Operators&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for a list of comparison operators, logical operators etc. that you can use in conditions.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>SORT</title>
      <link>https://www.montferret.dev/docs/fql/operators/high-level/sort/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://www.montferret.dev/docs/fql/operators/high-level/sort/</guid>
      <description>&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;sort&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;#sort&#34;&gt;&#xA;SORT&#xA;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;SORT&lt;/code&gt; statement will force a sort of the array of already produced intermediate results in the current block. &lt;code&gt;SORT&lt;/code&gt; allows specifying one or multiple sort criteria and directions. The general syntax is:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;columns&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;column is-full&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div id=&#34;code-232-text&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-text&#34; style=&#34;height: 80px;&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &#xA;SORT expression direction&#xA;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;script&gt;&#xA;        document.addEventListener(&#39;DOMContentLoaded&#39;, function () {&#xA;            const editor = ace.edit(&#39;code-232-text&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setTheme(&#34;ace/theme/tomorrow_night&#34;);&#xA;            editor.session.setMode(&#34;ace/mode/&#34; + &#39;aql&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setOptions({&#xA;                readOnly: true,&#xA;                highlightActiveLine: false,&#xA;                highlightGutterLine: false,&#xA;                displayIndentGuides: false,&#xA;                printMargin: false&#xA;            });&#xA;            editor.renderer.$cursorLayer.element.style.display = &#34;none&#34;&#xA;        }, false);&#xA;    &lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Example query that is sorting by lastName (in ascending order), then firstName (in ascending order), then by id (in descending order):&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>LIMIT</title>
      <link>https://www.montferret.dev/docs/fql/operators/high-level/limit/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://www.montferret.dev/docs/fql/operators/high-level/limit/</guid>
      <description>&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;limit&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;#limit&#34;&gt;&#xA;LIMIT&#xA;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;LIMIT&lt;/code&gt; statement allows slicing the result array using an offset and a count. It reduces the number of elements in the result to at most the specified number. Two general forms of &lt;code&gt;LIMIT&lt;/code&gt; are followed:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;columns&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;column is-full&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div id=&#34;code-822-text&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-text&#34; style=&#34;height: 100px;&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &#xA;LIMIT count&#xA;LIMIT offset, count&#xA;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;script&gt;&#xA;        document.addEventListener(&#39;DOMContentLoaded&#39;, function () {&#xA;            const editor = ace.edit(&#39;code-822-text&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setTheme(&#34;ace/theme/tomorrow_night&#34;);&#xA;            editor.session.setMode(&#34;ace/mode/&#34; + &#39;aql&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setOptions({&#xA;                readOnly: true,&#xA;                highlightActiveLine: false,&#xA;                highlightGutterLine: false,&#xA;                displayIndentGuides: false,&#xA;                printMargin: false&#xA;            });&#xA;            editor.renderer.$cursorLayer.element.style.display = &#34;none&#34;&#xA;        }, false);&#xA;    &lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The first form allows specifying only the count value whereas the second form allows specifying both offset and count. The first form is identical using the second form with an offset value of 0.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>LET</title>
      <link>https://www.montferret.dev/docs/fql/operators/high-level/let/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://www.montferret.dev/docs/fql/operators/high-level/let/</guid>
      <description>&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;let&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;#let&#34;&gt;&#xA;LET&#xA;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;LET&lt;/code&gt; statement can be used to assign an arbitrary value to a variable. The variable is then introduced in the scope the &lt;code&gt;LET&lt;/code&gt; statement is placed in.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The general syntax is:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;columns&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;column is-full&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div id=&#34;code-49-text&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-text&#34; style=&#34;height: 80px;&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &#xA;LET variableName = expression&#xA;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;script&gt;&#xA;        document.addEventListener(&#39;DOMContentLoaded&#39;, function () {&#xA;            const editor = ace.edit(&#39;code-49-text&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setTheme(&#34;ace/theme/tomorrow_night&#34;);&#xA;            editor.session.setMode(&#34;ace/mode/&#34; + &#39;aql&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setOptions({&#xA;                readOnly: true,&#xA;                highlightActiveLine: false,&#xA;                highlightGutterLine: false,&#xA;                displayIndentGuides: false,&#xA;                printMargin: false&#xA;            });&#xA;            editor.renderer.$cursorLayer.element.style.display = &#34;none&#34;&#xA;        }, false);&#xA;    &lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Variables are immutable in FQL, which means they can not be re-assigned:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>COLLECT</title>
      <link>https://www.montferret.dev/docs/fql/operators/high-level/collect/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://www.montferret.dev/docs/fql/operators/high-level/collect/</guid>
      <description>&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;collect&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;#collect&#34;&gt;&#xA;COLLECT&#xA;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;COLLECT&lt;/code&gt; keyword can be used to group an array by one or multiple group criteria.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;COLLECT&lt;/code&gt; statement will eliminate all local variables in the current scope. After &lt;code&gt;COLLECT&lt;/code&gt; only the variables introduced by &lt;code&gt;COLLECT&lt;/code&gt; itself are available.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;There are several syntax variants for &lt;code&gt;COLLECT&lt;/code&gt; operations:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-editor&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;columns&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;column is-full&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div id=&#34;code-555-text&#34; class=&#34;code-editor-text&#34; style=&#34;height: 230px;&#34;&gt;&#xA;                &#xA;COLLECT variableName = expression&#xA;COLLECT variableName = expression INTO groupsVariable&#xA;COLLECT variableName = expression INTO groupsVariable = projectionExpression&#xA;COLLECT variableName = expression INTO groupsVariable KEEP keepVariable&#xA;COLLECT variableName = expression WITH COUNT INTO countVariable&#xA;COLLECT variableName = expression AGGREGATE variableName = aggregateExpression&#xA;COLLECT variableName = expression AGGREGATE variableName = aggregateExpression INTO groupsVariable&#xA;COLLECT AGGREGATE variableName = aggregateExpression&#xA;COLLECT AGGREGATE variableName = aggregateExpression INTO groupsVariable&#xA;COLLECT WITH COUNT INTO countVariable&#xA;&#xA;            &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;script&gt;&#xA;        document.addEventListener(&#39;DOMContentLoaded&#39;, function () {&#xA;            const editor = ace.edit(&#39;code-555-text&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setTheme(&#34;ace/theme/tomorrow_night&#34;);&#xA;            editor.session.setMode(&#34;ace/mode/&#34; + &#39;aql&#39;);&#xA;            editor.setOptions({&#xA;                readOnly: true,&#xA;                highlightActiveLine: false,&#xA;                highlightGutterLine: false,&#xA;                displayIndentGuides: false,&#xA;                printMargin: false&#xA;            });&#xA;            editor.renderer.$cursorLayer.element.style.display = &#34;none&#34;&#xA;        }, false);&#xA;    &lt;/script&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;collect-grouping&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;#collect-grouping&#34;&gt;&#xA;Grouping syntaxes&#xA;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The first syntax form of &lt;code&gt;COLLECT&lt;/code&gt; only groups the result by the defined group criteria specified in expression. In order to further process the results produced by &lt;code&gt;COLLECT&lt;/code&gt;, a new variable (specified by &lt;code&gt;variableName&lt;/code&gt;) is introduced. This variable contains the group value.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
